## 5. Strengths

| # | Area | Details |
|---|------|---------|
| 1 | **Intelligent Multi-Phase Pipeline** | The 4-phase approach (extraction → code gen → execution → interpretation) is architecturally excellent. Instead of asking the LLM to analyze raw data (expensive and inaccurate), it generates executable pandas code, runs it in a sandbox, then has Gemini interpret computed results. This produces more accurate analyses at lower token cost. |
| 2 | **Real Authentication & Multi-User Support** | Supabase Auth with email/password signup, JWT verification via `@require_auth` decorator on all API routes. Per-user `UserState` isolated by `user_id` from JWT. Thread-safe `SessionManager` with `threading.Lock`. |
| 3 | **Persistent Storage Layer** | Supabase PostgreSQL with `profiles`, `chat_sessions`, `dashboard_configs` tables and Row Level Security. File uploads stored in Supabase Storage with per-user directory isolation. Session rehydration on login. |
| 4 | **Sandbox Security (Defense-in-Depth)** | `code_executor.py` implements 5 layers: code length cap (10K chars), AST-based static analysis via `_SafetyVisitor`, 19 blocked builtins + 9 forbidden modules + 14 forbidden attributes, subprocess isolation via `spawn` context, and a 60-second timeout. |
| 5 | **Smart Data Profiling** | `data_service.py` auto-detects dataset types (survey, time series, transactional, geographic, etc.) and generates domain-specific analysis suggestions. Provides the LLM with richer context, significantly improving output quality. |
| 6 | **Token-Efficient Context Building** | Schema context is dynamically sized with a `max_tokens` budget. Correlations are computed locally, only metadata sent to the LLM. The extraction phase pulls out unique categorical values so the code generator knows exact column names — prevents hallucinated column references. |
| 7 | **SSE Streaming Responses** | `/api/chat/stream` endpoint streams pipeline phases in real-time via Server-Sent Events. Frontend shows live progress updates (extracting → generating → executing → interpreting) instead of a static spinner. |
| 8 | **Graceful Degradation** | Code execution has 2 retry attempts with error feedback to Gemini, plus a text-only fallback (Phase 3). If code fails completely, users still get useful analysis. Cached results show a "Cached" badge for transparency. |
| 9 | **UX Polish** | Real-time streaming phases, follow-up suggestion chips, chart annotations (click to label), drag-and-drop dashboard with column spanning, fullscreen chart expansion with focus trap, data preview side panel, dark/light theme toggle with `prefers-color-scheme` auto-detection and localStorage persistence. |
| 10 | **Clean Modular CSS with Full Dark Mode** | Stylesheets split into 4 concerns: layout, chat, grid, overlays. Imported via a manifest (`dashboard.css`). CSS custom properties used for theming with complete `[data-theme="dark"]` overrides across all files. |
| 11 | **All Dependencies Pinned** | `requirements.txt` pins exact versions for all 10 packages — excellent for reproducibility and security. |
| 12 | **DOMPurify XSS Prevention** | All user-generated and LLM-generated markdown is sanitized through a `marked.js` → `DOMPurify` pipeline before DOM insertion. Custom `escapeHtml()` fallback if DOMPurify is unavailable. |
| 13 | **Per-User Query Caching** | LRU cache (300 items) per user with f-string keys prevents redundant API calls for repeated questions, saving both time and API costs. Thread-safe via `threading.Lock`. |
| 14 | **Easy Launch** | `start.bat` handles Python checks, dependency installation, server start, and browser launch in one click — low friction for non-technical users. |

