## 6. Weaknesses

### 6.1 Critical Issues

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | ~~**Massive Chat Pipeline Duplication**~~ | **RESOLVED** — Extracted shared `_run_analysis_pipeline()` generator consumed by both `chat()` (~15 lines) and `chat_stream()` (~15 lines). | `server.py` |
| 2 | **Thread-Unsafe Logout** | `logout()` mutates the shared Supabase singleton client's internal `_headers` attribute to inject user tokens before calling `sign_out()`. If two users log out simultaneously, headers can be interleaved. | `auth_service.py` lines 160-163 |
| 3 | **No DataFrame Caching** | `data_service.load_file()` re-downloads the full file from Supabase Storage on every call. Every chat message triggers a fresh download and parse. Adds latency and bandwidth cost per request. | `data_service.py` lines 52-76 |
| 4 | **No Session Eviction** | `SessionManager._sessions` grows unboundedly as new users authenticate. No TTL or eviction policy. `remove_state()` exists but is never called (not invoked on logout). Long-running servers will leak memory. | `app_state.py` |
| 5 | **No Full Data Pagination** | `get_full_data()` loads the entire dataset into memory and sends it as JSON. No pagination. Large files will cause memory and bandwidth issues. | `server.py` lines 317-328 |

### 6.2 Security Concerns

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **No Rate Limiting** | Chat, suggestion, and upload endpoints trigger expensive LLM calls. No throttling means easy API abuse/DoS. | `server.py` |
| 2 | **Zero SRI Hashes on All 6 CDN Resources** | Handsontable, SheetJS, Plotly.js, Marked.js, and DOMPurify all loaded without `integrity` or `crossorigin` attributes. A compromised CDN could inject arbitrary JavaScript with full access to auth tokens and data. | `dashboard.html` lines 15-23, 258 |
| 3 | **Unpinned CDN Versions** | SheetJS uses `xlsx-latest`, Handsontable and Marked.js use unpinned `npm/...` URLs. Supply-chain attack risk — malicious code could be injected via a version update with no safeguard. | `dashboard.html` |
| 4 | **localStorage Token Storage** | `dt_access_token`, `dt_refresh_token`, and `dt_user` stored in `localStorage`, accessible to any JS on the page including scripts from compromised CDNs. `httpOnly` cookies would be more secure. | `login.html` lines 309-311 |
| 5 | **No Prompt Injection Protection** | User questions are interpolated directly into LLM prompts. A crafted question could manipulate the system prompt, causing unintended code generation. | `gemini_service.py` |
| 6 | **Sandbox Escape Residual Risk** | While AST validation blocks known dangerous patterns, `type()`, `vars()`, `dir()`, and `hasattr()` remain in safe builtins. No memory or CPU limits on subprocess — malicious code could consume excessive resources. | `code_executor.py` |
| 7 | **No Token Refresh Endpoint** | The server returns `refresh_token` on login, but no endpoint exists to refresh an expired access token. Users must re-authenticate when tokens expire. | `auth_service.py` |
| 8 | **Token Verified via Network on Every Request** | `verify_token()` calls Supabase `getUser()` API on every authenticated request. No local JWT validation or caching. Adds latency and creates a dependency on Supabase availability. | `auth_service.py` line 130 |
| 9 | ~~**Duplicate Supabase Config**~~ | **RESOLVED** — Removed dead Supabase constants from `app_config.py`. `auth_service.py` is the single source of truth for Supabase credentials. Redundant `load_dotenv()` calls also removed from `auth_service.py` and `gemini_service.py` (kept only in `server.py`). | `app_config.py`, `auth_service.py` |

### 6.3 Performance Issues

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **File Re-Downloaded Per Chat Message** | Every chat query calls `load_file()` which downloads from Supabase Storage, parses, and builds the DataFrame from scratch. No in-memory caching of loaded DataFrames. | `data_service.py` |
| 2 | **DataFrame Copied Per Execution** | Full DataFrame is `.copy()`'d for every code execution call — doubles memory for large files. | `code_executor.py` |
| 3 | **O(n²) Correlation Computation** | Numeric correlation matrix computed for all column pairs — slow/expensive with 100+ columns. | `data_service.py` |
| 4 | **Subprocess Per Query** | A new Python process is spawned via `multiprocessing.get_context("spawn")` for every single chat query. Process creation overhead adds 0.5-1s per request. | `code_executor.py` |
| 5 | **Particle Animation O(n²)** | `connectParticles()` computes distance for every particle pair every frame. On 1920x1080: ~230 particles, ~26,000 comparisons per frame at 60fps. | `js/core.js` lines 221-257 |
| 6 | **Full Dashboard Grid Re-Render** | `renderDashboardGrid()` rebuilds entire grid HTML on every change (add, remove, reorder, resize), purging and re-creating all Plotly instances. | `js/dashboard-ui.js` |
| 7 | ~~**Unnecessary JS Loading on Landing Page**~~ | **RESOLVED** — `index.html` now only loads `core.js` (for particles). `data-chat.js` and `dashboard-ui.js` removed. | `index.html` |

